item.title: NMAT2526/04: Provision of Hoist Equipment and Services for Temporary Gallery
item.description:
The Museum requires the supply of Hoist Equipment and Services for Temporary Gallery.

The Museum has a large gallery space, the Temporary (1,000 m2) Gallery, which is used for temporary exhibitions.  The electric chain hoist systems have remained unchanged since their establishment in 2000, when the Museum building at Acton was constructed. As the systems and hoists are now at the end of their life and can no longer be supported, the Museum is undertaking an upgrade of the hoist systems and infrastructure, inclusive of cables, control systems and modular aluminium truss and cable management system.

item.title: CSIROEOI2026001: Parkes Observatory Cafe Services
item.description:
CSIRO is seeking Expressions of Interest (EOI) from suitably qualified and experienced service providers for the provision of café style food and beverage services (Services) for the café located at the CSIRO Parkes Observatory site. 

The site, located at 473 Telescope Road, Parkes NSW is one of CSIRO’s better-known sites and includes a café facility which has recently undergone a refurbishment.  

The site is home to Murriyang, CSIRO’s Parkes radio telescope; Giyalung Guluman, CSIRO’s 18-metre Parkes radio telescope and Giyalung Miil, CSIRO’s 12 metre Parkes radio telescope.   Murriyang, an icon of Australian science, has been in operation since 1961 and continues to be at the forefront of astronomical discovery.
